args: ...A fiend is demanding that you supply\nvillage women as sacrifices?!
Aye, that's right. It's a terrifying, cunning\nbeast that lives deep within the forest.
It has threatened to destroy our entire\nvillage unless we continue to gift it\nwith a supply of young maidens.
And so ya've been sendin' em for a\nwhile now...
I cannot imagine a more heinous crime\nthan a fiend who forces people to\nsurrender their loved ones!
This is not a matter we can simply\nwalk away from, {player_name}.
Oh, I wouldn't dream of it.
Right then. What is our plan?

From what we've heard, there are a
number of smaller fiends doing the
bidding of the one who is demanding
the sacrifices.

I think we can assume the leader will be
waiting in its den for the sacrifice, so the
question then becomes how to find it and
lure it out.
Bwaaa ha ha ha! Oh man, ol' Ranzal\njust had himself one HELL of an idea.
Experience tells me not to expect\novermuch from this.
Well, let's hear what he has to say.\nWhat's your plan, Ranzal?
Well, the first thing what we do is \nhand over a sacrifice like normal.
I knew this plan would be sheer idiocy.\nThat is what we are trying to STOP!

Don't get yer smallclothes in a bunch!
I ain't finished yet. The chief told us the
sacrifice gets taken back to the fiends'
den, yeah?
So we let 'em collect the sacrifice,\nfollow 'em back to their lair, then take\n'em out and save the day!
I don't know. It seems risky.

Also agreed. Yes, it would lead us to the
fiend's lair, but it would ALSO expose
whatever villager we use as our bait
to significant danger.
Oh, we ain't usin' a villager...
We're gonna use ME! Bwaaa ha ha!\nOh man, I am BRILLIANT sometimes!
Did you miss the part where the fiend\nhas been demanding young WOMEN?
It's a FIEND, not some egghead scientist!\nGimme a dress and slather some makeup\non and it'll never know the difference.
Oh, I think it very much will.
If this is to be our course of action,\nI shall stand in as the sacrifice.
Yes. Unlike a villager, I can more than\nhold my own in combat if necessary.
All right, we'll leave this to you.\nBut PLEASE be careful.
On my sacred honor as a Paladyn,\nI shall make this operation a success.
WHAT IS THE MEANING OF THIS?!
Clap shut your slackened jaws!\nI REFUSE to wear this absurd getup!

Er, but this is what we've been doing.
We choose a young woman from the
village and send her to the fiend clad
in our finest wedding dress.
The beast might suspect mischief\nif we change things up now.
You said nothing about this sacrifice\nbeing outfitted as the fiend's BRIDE.
Exactly what significance is there in such\nan extravagant outfit? I cannot imagine\nthis fiend cares how its food is dressed.
By wearing this dress, there can be\nno mistake on the fiend's part as to\nwho our chosen sacrifice is.
I see the logic in what you say...\nand yet I STILL refuse to wear this!
What's the problem? Ain't like this is the\nfirst time ya dressed up for a mission.
For what it's worth, Elly, you look pretty.\nMaybe just give it a try?
Th-that is a very mean-spirited joke,\nYour Highness.
I'm serious. Of course, you look good\nin pretty much whatever you wear.
And yet, it IS a stunning garment...
It's funny how much ya soften up when\nyer talkin' to {player_name}.
Again you seek to make me the\nsubject of your base mockery!
I will not stand for it, sir! Not today!
Cleo? What's wrong? Why are you crying?
I was just picturing what your wedding\nceremony will be like.
This must be how it feels when it is time\nfor one's daughter to get married! *sniiiff*
